    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1891-07-08T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1891-07-08T00:00:00-05:00" n="377" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d377">
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">Mr. <persName type="from">Adee</persName> to Mr.
                                <persName type="to">Denby</persName>
                    </hi>.</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Department
                                    of State</hi>,<lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1891-07-08">
                            <hi rend="italic">July 8,
                            1891</hi>
                        </date>.</dateline>
                    <seg rendition="#left">No. 637.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Sir</hi>: The Department has to commend your efforts
                        toward securing due protection for our citizens in China, whose lives were
                        endangered by the late riots, as reported in your No. 1314, of the 28th of
                        May last, acknowledging at the same time your No. 1311 of 25th, and your No.
                        1312 of 27th of May, relating particulars of the riots.</p>
                <p>I am, etc.,</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Alvey A. Adee</hi>,<lb/>
                        <hi rend="italic">Acting Secretary</hi>.</signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
